I'm working on a @{FG "Shine"}hardware project@{FG "Text"} of an amiga-controlled dataswitch.
The project lets you switch up to 8 parallel and 6 serial ports (using only
one of them, this is a switch not a multi-I/O). The interesting things are
that the switching is software controlled (there will be also an ARexx port)
and the project is modular: you build only the ports needed, and you can
easily add another port by adding another module. The hardware is almost
done, but I must write the software and the documentation. The project is
very time consuming, and I haven't much spare time.
I think to publish it if I'll receive enough feedback from this program 
(that is: postcards). So if you want to support me, please send the 
@{"postcard" LINK "Distribution"}... Thank you.

This program was inspired by MergeRecent (of Alex Tucker). The first release
was infact a rewrite in AmigaE and bug-fix of his program. Now it is quite
different, having many useful options and (I hope) no more bugs.

