@NODE "Headers" "Headers of output files"
@TOC "MAIN"

The header of the new index
***************************

The index files produced by MergeRec have a header different from the
original Aminet Index. Here is an example:


  | Updated Aminet Index on 24-Dec-95. Ages correct up to 22-Dec-95
  | Original Index date: 15-Dec-95
  | The list is sorted by directory and file name
  | This site, ftp.slownet.empty.gag, contains almost nothing
  | Age measured in weeks before creation of this index.
  |
  |File                Dir        Size Age Description
  |------------------- ---        ---- --- -----------


These are the meanings:

Updated Aminet Index..  date of the last RECENT file used for the update.
Original Inded date..   date of the original index used for the first update.
Ages correct up to..    date used by MergeRec to avoid errors in the "Age"
                        column if you update after less than a week. It is
                        modified only if the RECENT date and this date
                        differ for more than 6 days.


The header of the SAVERECENT file
*********************************

By default, if MergeRec finds more than one recent in the input file and
the @{"NOSORT" LINK "NOSORT"} switch is off, the header of the resulting SAVERECENT
file is changed, to reflect the merge process. The header report which
recent list were found by MergeRec in the input file.

You can strip this header using the @{"NRH" LINK "NRH"} switch.
Here is an example:

  | Recent uploads to Aminet on 21-Jan-96
  | This file was built by merging the following recent lists:
  | Daily on 15-Jan-96
  | Daily on 18-Jan-96
  | Weekly on 21-Jan-96
  |
  |File              Dir        Size Description
  |----------------- ---        ---- -----------


The header of the SAVENEWS file
*******************************

This file has also a header different to the RECENT list. The date reported
in the first line is the same of the RECENTFILE.

You can strip this header using the @{"NNH" LINK "NNH"} switch.

  | New aminet uploads on <date>
  |
  |File              Dir        Size Description
  |----------------- ---        ---- -----------

@ENDNODE

@NODE "History" "History"
@TOC "MAIN"

Changes from v1.1
*****************

The @{FG "Shine"}template is changed@{FG "Text"}. See @{"Usage" LINK "Usage"}.

New options/features:

- Removed the limit of one recent per input file. Now you can give a file
  with multiple recents (typically the daily-recents).

- @{"Save" LINK "SR"} (or append) the extracted RECENT (sorted or not) to a file.
  If multiple recents are found they can be merged together.

- @{"Compare" LINK "SN"} the RECENT file to your INDEX, and save to a file those entries
  that are really new uploads.

- @{"Replace" LINK "REP"} the old index with the new (you don't have to manually delete
  the old index and rename the new)

Bugs/problems fixed:

- If the Workbench was localized with a non-english language, MergeRec
  didn't read the dates in the headers (unless the month name was 
  translated to the preset language).

- The age column was not updated correctly (if you updated the index after
  less than a week, the age remained always unchanged). Now the age column
  is always correct (with a tolerance of +/- 1 week), even if you update
  daily the index.

- There was a bug in the sort routine (it was the MergeRecent routine buggy):
  the first entry of a recent was not sorted.

- Better recognition of end of recent list.

History
*******

v1.0   3-Dec-95  (internal)
                 Bug-fix and C to E conversion of MergeRecent.

v1.1   5-Dec-95  (first aminet release)
                 Added the CR stripping and pre-header skipping.
                 It has a bug: if the WB is localized (using a language
                 different from engligh) the program can't read the
                 dates in the files.                

v1.2  29-Dec-95  (internal)
                 Fixed date reading bug if WB localized.

v1.3  30-Dec-95  (internal)
                 Changed template, added SR, APP, STAT, UPD options.
                 Doc now in guide format.

v1.4  30-Dec-95  (internal)
                 Removed the problem when updating the index after less
                 than a week (doing this on older version of MergeRec,
                 caused an error in the age column, never updated).

v1.5   2-Jan-96  (internal)
                 Added STDOUT, NOSORT and SAVENEWS options, changed the
                 names of UPDATEINDEX option to REPLACE. Some other minor
                 changes.

v1.5a  5-Jan-96  (internal)
                 Removed bug of v1.5 (replace option not working).

v2.0  25-Jan-96  (second aminet release)
                 Remove sort bug (a MergeRecent bug), added NRH, NNH switches,
                 multiple recent support, improved end of recent recognition.
@ENDNODE

